summary:
The Security Council, recalling its previous resolutions on Libya, adopted Resolution 2208 (2015) at its 7399th meeting on 5 March 2015. The Council: 
- Extended until 31 March 2015 the authorizations provided by and measures imposed by resolution 2146 (2014); 
- Extended until 31 March 2015 the mandate of the UN Support Mission in Libya (UNSMIL), under the leadership of the Special Representative of the Secretary-General; 
- Decided to remain seized of the matter, supporting efforts for a political solution to challenges facing Libya.
